Bring a large #pot{} of salted water to a boil. Preheat broiler to high. Wash and dry all produce. Cut @zucchini{1}(cut into ¼-inch cubes). Cut @fresh mozzarella{4%oz}(cut into ½-inch cubes). Halve, peel, and chop @yellow onion{1}(halved, peeled, and chopped). Mince or grate @garlic{2%cloves}(minced or grated). Pick half the @basil{½%oz}(leaves picked and roughly chopped) leaves from stems and roughly chop (save the rest for garnish).

Once water boils, add @penne pasta{6%oz} to pot. Cook until al dente, ~{9-11%minutes}. Carefully scoop out ½ cup pasta cooking water, then drain.

Meanwhile, heat a large drizzle of @olive oil{1%tbsp} in a large pan over medium-high heat (use an #ovenproof pan{} if you have one). Add zucchini and cook, stirring, until just browned, about ~{5%minutes}. Add onion, garlic, and half the @Tuscan Heat Spice{1%tbsp} (we'll use the rest later). Cook, stirring, until softened, ~{3-5%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Add @marinara cup{14%oz}, penne, remaining Tuscan Heat Spice, and reserved pasta cooking water to pan and stir to combine. Let simmer until warmed through, ~{3-4%minutes}. Stir in chopped basil and half the @Parmesan cheese{¼%cup}. Season with plenty of salt and pepper.

> TIP: If your pan is not ovenproof, transfer contents to an 8-by-11-inch baking dish at this point. For 4 servings, transfer to a 9-by-13-inch baking dish.

Scatter mozzarella over pasta in pan or dish. In a #small bowl{}, combine @panko breadcrumbs{¼%cup}, remaining Parmesan, and a drizzle of olive oil, then sprinkle over pasta.

Place pan or #baking dish{} under broiler and broil until panko is golden brown and sauce is bubbly, ~{5-7%minutes}.

> TIP: Keep an eye out for any burning.

Let cool slightly. Tear remaining basil leaves and scatter over top. Divide between bowls or plates and serve.